<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,626,1481]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis box="[136,204,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Herbs</emphasis>
, 
<quantity box="[220,332,626,653]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" unit="cm" value="40.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="20.0">20–60 cm</quantity>
alt. 
<emphasis box="[384,490,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Branches</emphasis>
vinaceous, cylindrical, costate. 
<emphasis box="[854,932,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Leaves</emphasis>
opposite, sessile, concolorous and vinaceous, blades 0.3–3 × 
<quantity box="[321,454,662,689]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" unit="cm" value="0.44999999999999996" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.6 cm</quantity>
, lanceolate, coriaceous, pubescent, attenuate at base, acute at apex, entire at margin. 
<emphasis box="[136,286,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Inflorescence</emphasis>
in terminal cymes, 11–30-flowered, peduncle 
<quantity box="[807,915,698,725]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.1" metricValueMax="9.2" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" unit="cm" value="6.1" valueMax="9.2" valueMin="3.0">3–9.2 cm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[925,1017,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Flowers</emphasis>
homostylous, 4-merous, pedicel 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.85" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" unit="cm" value="3.85" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="0.7">0.7–7 cm</quantity>
; calyx 1.1–1.7 × 
<quantity box="[371,500,734,761]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7" metricValueMax="13.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" unit="cm" value="0.7" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="0.1">0.1–1.3 cm</quantity>
, vinaceous, winged, keeled, campanulate, pubescent; corolla purplish, campanulate, tube 1.1–1.5 × 
<quantity box="[319,453,770,797]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" unit="cm" value="0.75" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.6">0.6–0.9 cm</quantity>
; lobes 
<quantity box="[540,672,770,797]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" unit="cm" value="0.6" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.8 cm</quantity>
, at base elliptical to ovate, at apex rounded; stamens 
<quantity box="[1314,1447,770,797]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" unit="cm" value="0.35" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.1">0.1–0.6 cm</quantity>
, heterodynamous, adnate, conation 
<quantity box="[530,598,806,833]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
, anthers dorsifixed; ovary 5 × 
<quantity box="[948,1016,806,833]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
, style ca. 
<quantity box="[1130,1199,807,833]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
, stigma bilobed. 
<emphasis box="[1394,1452,807,832]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Fruit</emphasis>
septifragal capsule.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="75" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,626,1481]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,496,878,904]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Habitat and distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName box="[531,798,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Shulthesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pachyphylla">
<emphasis box="[531,798,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Shulthesia pachyphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Chapada 
<taxonomicName box="[1100,1231,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Diamantina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Diamantina</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Guimaraes, E. F." box="[1252,1447,878,904]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" refId="ref15178" refString="Guimaraes, E. F. (2002) Schultesia Mart. (Gentianaceae) - Revisao taxonomica. Universidade Federal do Rio de Janeiro / Museu Nacional, Rio de Janeiro, 356 pp." type="book" year="2002">Guimarães 2002</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." box="[136,368,914,940]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis box="[239,298,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
), considered rare (
<bibRefCitation author="Calio, M. F. A. &amp; Guimaraes, E. F." box="[582,876,914,940]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" pagination="185 - 186" refId="ref12762" refString="Calio, M. F. A. &amp; Guimaraes, E. F. (2009) Gentianaceae. In: Giulietti, A. M., Rapini, A., Andrade, M. J. G., Queiroz, L. P. &amp; Silva, J. M. C. (Eds.) Plantas raras do Brasil. Conservacao Internacional, Belo Horizonte. pp. 185 - 186." type="book chapter" year="2009">Calió &amp; Guimarães 2009</bibRefCitation>
), occurring in the cities of Abaíra, Andaraí, Barra da Estiva, Cascavel, Ibicoara, Itaeté, Jacobina, Lençóis, Miguel Calmon, Morro do Chapéu, Mucugê, Palmeiras, Piatã and Pindobaçu in areas of “campo rupestre” with altitudes above 
<quantity box="[953,1026,986,1013]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" unit="m" value="700.0">700 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." box="[1043,1275,986,1012]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis box="[1147,1205,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). In the present study, the distribution modeling analysis revealed high suitability for the occurrence in the Chapada 
<taxonomicName box="[1272,1403,1022,1048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Diamantina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Diamantina</taxonomicName>
and surroundings. Furthermore, a moderate for high suitability was also recovered in the border area between the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[136,201,1094,1120]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Bahia</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[258,413,1094,1120]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, what allows extrapolations of possible occurrence of the species also in the Serra Geral de Licínio de Almeida, locality compared in this study (
<figureCitation box="[727,793,1130,1156]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1815,1837]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,200,1767]" captionTargetId="figure-22@2.[151,1436,187,1788]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Parque Municipal de Mucugê—Projeto Sempre Viva (PMM), Bahia, Brazil. Map of the study area, evidencing the location of PMM and other areas of the Espinhaço Range (ER) used for comparison in this study (A), “campo rupestre” phytophysiognomy (B). Photo B by Ariane Leite. Legend: (Lilac area) ER above 1000 m a.s.l." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5424487/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[807,895,1130,1156]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1661,1683]" captionTargetBox="[444,1147,867,1622]" captionTargetId="figure-307@7.[434,1153,857,1637]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Maps of occurrence with localities used for the species distribution modeling, showing the study area location within South America. Curtia diffusa (A), Macrocarpaea illecebrosa (B), Prepusa montana (C), Schultesia bahiensis (D), Schultesia crenuliflora (E), Schultesia minensis (F), Schultesia pachyphylla (G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5424489/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[907,995,1130,1156]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="15.[136,229,1180,1202]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,1155]" captionTargetId="figure-19@15.[151,1436,190,1155]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 4. Maps of environmental suitability of native/endemic species of Gentianaceae in the Espinhaço Range (ER): Curtia diffusa (A), Macrocarpaea illecebrosa (B), Prepusa montana (C), Schultesia bahiensis (D), Schultesia crenuliflora (E), Schultesia minensis (F), Schultesia pachyphylla (G)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424493" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5424493/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
, Appendix 1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="75" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,626,1481]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,1166,1192]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Comments</emphasis>
:—It presents trichomes on the leaves and the calyx, unlike 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gilg" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="Chamisso &amp; Schlechtendal" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[966,1284,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Calolisianthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pedunculatus">
<emphasis box="[966,1284,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Calolisianthus pedunculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Chelonanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpuracens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Chelonanthus purpuracens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Knoblauch" authorityYear="1894" box="[290,476,1202,1229]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Curtia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis box="[290,476,1202,1229]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Curtia tenuifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Knoblauch" authorityYear="1894" box="[489,699,1202,1229]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Curtia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verticillaris">
<emphasis box="[489,699,1202,1229]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Curtia verticillaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guimaraes &amp; Fontella" authorityYear="2001" box="[712,938,1202,1228]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Schultesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bahiensis">
<emphasis box="[712,938,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Schultesia bahiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Siqueira et al. 2014)" baseAuthorityName="Siqueira" baseAuthorityYear="2014" box="[990,1393,1202,1229]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gentianaceae" genus="Schultesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crenuliflora">
<emphasis box="[990,1150,1202,1229]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">S. crenuliflora</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." box="[1163,1385,1202,1228]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis box="[1264,1319,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This species can also be identified by the vinaceous calyx and hypocrateriform corolla, white internally and lilac at the apex of the lobes (
<bibRefCitation author="Siqueira, G. B. &amp; Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A." box="[281,507,1274,1301]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref17510" refString="Siqueira, G. B., Espirito Santo, F. B. &amp; Rapini, A. (2014) Flora da Bahia: Gentianaceae. Sitientibus serie Ciencias Biologicas 14: 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.13102 / scb 295" type="journal article" year="2014">
Siqueira 
<emphasis box="[383,433,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,626,1481]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,440,1310,1336]" pageId="14" pageNumber="75">Specimens examined</emphasis>
